Interface Dictionary

  • All Superinterfaces:

    All Known Subinterfaces:

    All Known Implementing Classes:

    public interface Dictionary
extends Iterable<String>
    A dictionary provides a bidirectional mapping terms (Strings) and term ids (integers). The semantics of the mapping is left unspecified, but the iteration order is always in increasing term id.
    Author:
    Jimmy Lin
